{"title_page": "SkyWheel Helsinki", "text_new": "{{short description|Ferris wheel in Helsinki}}\n{{Infobox building\n| name = SkyWheel Helsinki\n| image = File:Finniar SkyWheel Helsinki (Ferris wheel) (2).jpg\n| location = [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]]\n| status = Operating\n| building_type = [[Ferris wheel]]\n| opened_date = {{Start date and age|2014|06|03}}\n| height = {{Convert|40|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}\n| former_names = Finnair SkyWheel\n| owner = Skywheel Helsinki Oy\n| website = http://skywheel.fi/en/\n| coordinates = {{coord|60|10|1.8|N|24|57|35.2|E|region:FI|display=title,inline}}\n| address = Katajanokanlaituri 2\n}}\n\n'''SkyWheel Helsinki''' is a 40-meter (131 feet) tall [[Ferris wheel]] in central [[Helsinki|Helsinki, Finland]]. One of its gondola cabins, the SkySauna, is the world's first [[sauna]] on a Ferris wheel.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/05/17/finland-launches-rival-to-the-london-eye---with-a-sauna-cabin/|title=Finland launches rival to the London Eye - with a sauna cabin|last=Orange|first=Richard|date=2016-05-17|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2019-11-25|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref> It opened to the public on June 3, 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/travel/la-trb-finland-skywheel-20140602-story.html|title=Finland: Get a good look at Helsinki from newly opened SkyWheel|date=2014-06-03|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> It was originally named the Finnair SkyWheel and its placement on [[Katajanokka]] harbor is where the airline first located its flight operations in the 1920s.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.finnairgroup.com/mediaen/mediaen_7.html?Id=xml_1622804.html|title=Finnair SkyWheel arrives in Helsinki|date=2014-07-25|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140725200723/http://www.finnairgroup.com/mediaen/mediaen_7.html?Id=xml_1622804.html|archive-date=2014-07-25|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref>\n\n== Design ==\n\nThe Netherlands-based Dutch Wheels designed and constructed the wheel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.seattlepi.com/national/article/Helsinki-s-Finnair-Skywheel-joins-the-world-s-5526232.php|title=Helsinki's 'Finnair Skywheel' joins the world's great wheels|last=Cohen|first=Aubrey|date=2014-06-03|website=seattlepi.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> It is a model R40.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dutchwheels.com/index.php/products/r-series|title=R-Series|date=2015-08-14|website=web.archive.org|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150814015321/http://dutchwheels.com/index.php/products/r-series|archive-date=2015-08-14|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> It has 30 climate controlled gondolas, allowing the wheel to operate year-round.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/zL9rl9|title=S\u00e4tt kurs mot en ny h\u00f6jdare i Helsingfors|date=2014-06-17|website=Aftonbladet|language=sv|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> Of these, 29 blue-and-white gondolas can accommodate six people, except for the VIP gondola which can accommodate four.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://skywheel.fi/en/services|title=SkyWheel Helsinki|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> The [[wood paneling|wood paneled]] SkySauna gondola can hold up to five people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysauna.fi/|title=SkySauna|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> The VIP gondola features a glass floor and leather chairs.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Commons-inline|Finnair SkyWheel}}\n*{{Official website|http://skywheel.fi/en/}} {{in lang|en}}\n\n[[Category:Ferris wheels]]\n[[Category:Helsinki]]\n[[Category:Sauna]]\n[[Category:Landmarks in Finland]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Ferris wheel in Helsinki}}\n{{Infobox building\n| name = SkyWheel Helsinki\n| image = File:Finniar SkyWheel Helsinki (Ferris wheel) (2).jpg\n| location = [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]]\n| status = Operating\n| building_type = [[Ferris wheel]]\n| opened_date = {{Start date and age|2014|06|03}}\n| height = {{Convert|40|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}\n| former_names = Finnair SkyWheel\n| owner = Skywheel Helsinki Oy\n| website = http://skywheel.fi/en/\n| coordinates = {{coord|60|10|1.8|N|24|57|35.2|E|region:FI|display=title,inline}}\n| address = Katajanokanlaituri 2\n}}\n\n'''SkyWheel Helsinki''' is a 40-meter (131 feet) tall [[Ferris wheel]] in central [[Helsinki|Helsinki, Finland]]. One of its gondola cabins, the SkySauna, is the world's first [[sauna]] on a Ferris wheel.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/05/17/finland-launches-rival-to-the-london-eye---with-a-sauna-cabin/|title=Finland launches rival to the London Eye - with a sauna cabin|last=Orange|first=Richard|date=2016-05-17|work=The Telegraph|access-date=2019-11-25|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235}}</ref> It opened to the public on June 3, 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/travel/la-trb-finland-skywheel-20140602-story.html|title=Finland: Get a good look at Helsinki from newly opened SkyWheel|date=2014-06-03|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> It was originally named the Finnair SkyWheel and its placement on [[Katajanokka]] harbor is where the airline first located its flight operations in the 1920s.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.finnairgroup.com/mediaen/mediaen_7.html?Id=xml_1622804.html|title=Finnair SkyWheel arrives in Helsinki|date=2014-07-25|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140725200723/http://www.finnairgroup.com/mediaen/mediaen_7.html?Id=xml_1622804.html|archive-date=2014-07-25|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref>\n\n== Design ==\n\nThe Netherlands-based Dutch Wheels designed and constructed the wheel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.seattlepi.com/national/article/Helsinki-s-Finnair-Skywheel-joins-the-world-s-5526232.php|title=Helsinki's 'Finnair Skywheel' joins the world's great wheels|last=Cohen|first=Aubrey|date=2014-06-03|website=seattlepi.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> It is a model R40.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dutchwheels.com/index.php/products/r-series|title=R-Series|date=2015-08-14|website=web.archive.org|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150814015321/http://dutchwheels.com/index.php/products/r-series|archive-date=2015-08-14|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> It has 30 climate controlled gondolas, allowing the wheel to operate year round.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/zL9rl9|title=S\u00e4tt kurs mot en ny h\u00f6jdare i Helsingfors|date=2014-06-17|website=Aftonbladet|language=sv|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> Of these, 29 blue-and-white gondolas can accommodate six people, except for the VIP gondola which can accommodate four.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://skywheel.fi/en/services|title=SkyWheel Helsinki|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> The [[wood paneling|wood paneled]] SkySauna gondola can hold up to five people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysauna.fi/|title=SkySauna|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-11-25}}</ref> The VIP gondola features a glass floor and leather chairs.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Commons-inline|Finnair SkyWheel}}\n*{{Official website|http://skywheel.fi/en/}} {{in lang|en}}\n\n\n[[Category:Ferris wheels]]\n[[Category:Helsinki]]\n[[Category:Sauna]]\n[[Category:Landmarks in Finland]]\n", "name_user": "Majavah", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: year round \u2192 year-round", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SkyWheel_Helsinki"}
